            "subject": "LU-14366 mdt: lfs mkdir should return -EEXIST if exists"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Li Dongyang",
          "email": "dongyangli@ddn.com",
          "date": "2021-03-19 09:26:28.000000000",
          "tz": 660
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2021-04-15 06:30:32.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-14536 o2iblnd: don't resend if there's no listener",
        "message": "LU-14536 o2iblnd: don't resend if there's no listener\n\nIf there's no listener at remote peer, we will\nget IB_CM_REJ_INVALID_SERVICE_ID, currently we\nwill try to resend which makes the discovery longer\nthan necessary when connecting to a node which is\nnot up.\nUse -EHOSTUNREACH instead of -ECONNREFUSED,\nso we don't end up queued for resend.\n\nChange-Id: Ifaf14bc3ada2e2469669285917e366af669817e2\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Li Dongyang <dongyangli@ddn.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/42109\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
